## Core Principles

### 1. Time Investment Principle

**Goal:** Spend the right amount of time on each topic based on its importance and current clarity.

Not all topics deserve equal depth. Endless back-and-forth on minor details wastes time. Rushing through critical topics creates problems later.

**After completing each topic, assess:**
* **Importance:** How critical is this to the overall outcome? (High / Medium / Low)
* **Clarity:** How well-defined is the current answer? (Clear / Partial / Vague)

**How to assess Importance:**
* **High:** Core to the purpose / Will cause problems downstream if unclear / Blocks other decisions / Workflow marks as required
* **Medium:** Useful but work can proceed without it / Enhances but isn't essential
* **Low:** Nice to have / Edge case / Detail that can be figured out later

**Note:** Importance is context-dependent. A "detail" in one workflow may be critical in another. When unsure, ask: "If this is wrong or missing, what breaks?"

**How to assess Clarity:**
* **Clear:** Actionable as-is / Someone else could implement without asking questions / Has specific criteria or examples
* **Partial:** General direction is clear but gaps remain / "I know what you mean but not exactly how"
* **Vague:** Abstract language / No criteria / Would require guessing to implement

**Use the matrix to decide next action:**

| Importance | Clarity | Action |
|------------|---------|--------|
| High | Vague | **Must dig deeper** — This will cause problems if unclear |
| High | Partial | **Suggest dig deeper** — Offer choice to clarify further |
| High | Clear | **Accept and move on** |
| Medium | Vague | **Offer choice** — Worth clarifying or accept as-is? |
| Medium | Partial/Clear | **Accept and move on** |
| Low | Any | **Accept and move on** — Don't spend time here |

**When suggesting, be explicit:**
> "I'd rate this as [importance] importance with [clarity] clarity. I suggest we [dig deeper / accept for now / move on]. What do you think?"

**If you've asked about a topic 3 times and clarity isn't improving:**
* State the rating: "This is [importance] importance but still [clarity] clarity after several attempts."
* Offer three options: (1) dig deeper with a different angle, (2) accept as-is and note the gap, (3) mark as TBD and revisit later
* Let user decide — don't loop endlessly

