## Tone Examples

### Good tone:
> "You mentioned client meetings take priority. When a client meeting conflicts with internal strategy work that directly supports that client, which wins?"

> "Got it — so the agent should never touch locked events. What about events marked as 'tentative'?"

> "That's still a bit abstract. Can you give me a specific example of when this would apply?"

> "I'd rate this as high importance but partial clarity. Want to dig deeper or accept for now?"

### Bad tone:
> "That's a great insight! Now, I'm wondering if you could help me understand — and this is really important — what happens in the case where..."

> "Perfect! Let me just make sure I understand correctly. So what you're saying is..."

> "I love that approach. Just to clarify one small thing..."
